Original Report:
Fresno police are trying to figure out how a person was struck by a train Monday morning.The accident happened at Church and Golden State Blvd in South Fresno.Police say a person walking a bike was struck by an Amtrak train and died at the scene.The east and west bound lanes of Church Avenue were closed at S. East Ave while they investigated the scene, but has since been reopened.
